'''Pieter-Steyn de Wet''' (born 8 January 1991) is a [[South Africa]]n [[rugby union]] player for {{Rut Aurillac}} in the French [[Rugby Pro D2|Pro D2]].<ref name="SARU Player Profile Pieter-Steyn de Wet">{{SA Rugby Player Profile | id=51999 | name=Pieter-Steyn de Wet | date=4 June 2016}}</ref> His usual position is [[Rugby union positions#Fly-half|fly-half]].

De Wet represented the [[University of the Free State|Shimlas]] in the [[2013 Varsity Rugby|2013 Varsity Cup season]] making 6 appearances. He also previously made 4 substitute appearances for the [[Free State Cheetahs]] during the [[2012 Vodacom Cup]].

In April 2013 he moved west to join the {{Rut Griquas}} who were suffering a fly-half crisis due to [[Burton Francis]] and [[Francois Brummer]] being called into the {{Rut Cheetahs}} [[Super Rugby]] squad. He made his debut in a 47–31 defeat to the {{Rut Pumas}} on 5 April 2013<ref name="GWK Griquas 31-47 Steval Pumas">{{SA Rugby Match Centre | id=104054 | homeid=11664 | awayid=11644 | leagueid=1164 | hometeam=GWK Griquas | homescore=31 | awayscore=47 | awayteam=Steval Pumas | matchdate=5 April 2013 | date=3 June 2016}}</ref><ref name="Pieter-Steyn de Wet to make Griquas debut">{{cite web | work=OFM.co.za | url=http://www.ofm.co.za/article/130220/PieterSteyn-de-Wet-to-make-Griquas-debut | title=Pieter-Steyn de Wet to make Griquas debut |accessdate=8 April 2013}}</ref> and made five starts, but was released back to {{Rut UFS Shimlas}} before the [[2013 Currie Cup Premier Division]].<ref name="Geen GW-kontrakte vir Horn, Carney en drietal van Shimlas">{{cite web | url=http://www.beeld.com/sport/2013-05-06-geen-gw-kontrakte-vir-horn-carney-en-drietal-van-shimlas | title=Geen GW-kontrakte vir Horn, Carney en drietal van Shimlas | publisher=Media24 | work=Beeld | date=7 May 2013 | accessdate=7 May 2013 | language=Afrikaans}}</ref>

